Key Match Events: Bobby Miller pitched five strong innings, giving up two hits and allowing three runs.
Shohei Ohtani went 0-for-5, a night after hitting his 42nd home run and stealing his 41st and 42nd bases.
The Dodgers put up four runs on five hits in the fourth inning.
Colton Cowser hit a three-run home run for the Orioles.
Blake Treinen struck out Gunnar Henderson with the bases loaded to end the seventh inning.
Tommy Edman's sacrifice fly in the eighth extended the Dodgers' lead to 6-3.
